title: The Marne: a tale of the war
creator: Edith Wharton
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Marne: a tale of the war by Edith Wharton. Read by Elizabeth Klett. American writer Edith Wharton is known for her novels of manners set in old New York; yet much of her adult life was spent in France. She lived in Paris throughout World War I and was heavily involved in refugee work. Her 1918 novella The Marne dramatizes the events of the war as seen through the eyes of 15-year-old Troy Belknap, an American boy who longs to join up and save his beloved France. (Summary by Elizabeth Klett) For more free audio books, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
